1
00:00:00,292 --> 00:00:02,083
My name is Aladdin Khaled Ahmad

2
00:00:02,918 --> 00:00:04,959
I live in the Nabi Jirjis area

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:10,500
I used to work as an assistant in a pharmacy

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,125
And I had a shop with a lot of secondhand medicine

5
00:00:17,417 --> 00:00:20,209
People would bring it to me, and I distributed it for free

6
00:00:22,334 --> 00:00:25,709
This medicine was in my shop during the time of ISIS

7
00:00:26,125 --> 00:00:28,500
I distributed it for free to the poor

8
00:00:32,334 --> 00:00:38,375
Those who called themselves the Islamic State arrested me

9
00:00:38,959 --> 00:00:42,375
They brought me from this street and took me into the church

10
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,334
Interviewer: Tell me your date of birth

11
00:00:45,959 --> 00:00:48,542
I was born in 1973

12
00:00:49,626 --> 00:00:54,459
I am married and I have five children, three sons and two daughters

13
00:00:55,542 --> 00:01:01,375
Interviewer: Did anything happen before they detained you?

14
00:01:01,876 --> 00:01:04,375
Did they do something specific or give you a warning?

15
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:08,751
No, earlier they caught me twice because of cigarettes, and I was released

16
00:01:08,834 --> 00:01:13,375
After that they interrogated me, then a few days later they came and took me

17
00:01:14,292 --> 00:01:16,918
Interviewer: When they detained you, do you think someone informed on you?

18
00:01:17,125 --> 00:01:19,959
Or do you think you were being watched, or something else?

19
00:01:20,250 --> 00:01:21,918
I think I was being watched

20
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:27,167
Maybe I was monitored, but I didn’t do anything

21
00:01:29,834 --> 00:01:32,500
Interviewer: When they arrested you at your house and they brought you here

22
00:01:32,584 --> 00:01:33,959
They took me from the shop, not from the house

23
00:01:33,959 --> 00:01:35,042
Interviewer: Sorry, from the shop

24
00:01:35,042 --> 00:01:37,542
When they brought you, did they put you in a car?

25
00:01:37,542 --> 00:01:41,125
Or since the place was close, did they bring you on foot?

26
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:46,292
Interviewer: And when they brought you, did they tie your hands and blindfold you?
Witness: No

27
00:01:46,334 --> 00:01:50,167
Interviewer: Did they use bad words or insults with you?

28
00:01:50,417 --> 00:01:53,500
And did they deal with you angrily?

29
00:01:53,834 --> 00:01:58,292
Did they beat you while arresting you and bringing you to this prison?

30
00:01:58,334 --> 00:02:00,292
The beating happened inside the church

31
00:02:00,292 --> 00:02:02,083
Interviewer: And did that happen on the way here?

32
00:02:02,125 --> 00:02:04,626
No, they didn’t beat me in front of people

33
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:07,751
Interviewer: Can you describe the appearance of the two who came to you?

34
00:02:07,751 --> 00:02:10,334
What were their ages? Were they from Mosul?

35
00:02:10,375 --> 00:02:12,709
Or from its outskirts, or from outside it?

36
00:02:14,083 --> 00:02:15,083
They were from Mosul

37
00:02:15,918 --> 00:02:17,334
Interviewer: What were their ages?

38
00:02:17,375 --> 00:02:20,834
One of them was about 38 years old

39
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:23,209
And the other was about 30

40
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:26,626
Interviewer: Do you remember what clothes they were wearing?

41
00:02:26,626 --> 00:02:27,626
The Kandahari outfit

42
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:31,375
Interviewer: And they brought you here

43
00:02:31,375 --> 00:02:32,459
Yes, they brought me here

44
00:02:32,626 --> 00:02:33,709
Interviewer: Around what time?

45
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,334
Around 11 in the morning

46
00:02:38,042 --> 00:02:40,500
Interviewer: When they brought you here, did they come inside the prison with you?

47
00:02:40,542 --> 00:02:42,042
Or did they hand you over to other people?

48
00:02:42,042 --> 00:02:43,292
They handed me over to other people

49
00:02:43,709 --> 00:02:45,209
To people from security
